      { type: "h2", text: `Capital Trap` },
      { type: "p", text: `The lethal, widely accepted assumption in the manufacturing sector that massive capital expenditure (buying a machine, leasing a building, cutting steel tooling) is the mandatory prerequisite to testing a new market opportunity.` },
      { type: "h2", text: `Confidence (vs. Evidence)` },
      { type: "p", text: `The mathematical certainty built through active market testing. Smart leadership teams seek confidence about the future, rather than demanding historical evidence, because historical evidence of a new, highly differentiated strategy does not exist until it is too late.` },
