      { type: "p", text: `The most valuable asset a mid-sized company possesses: the ability to look at the market, realize a hypothesis was wrong, and instantly pivot the strategy without bankrupting the company.` },
      { type: "h2", text: `Strategic Learning Habit` },
      { type: "p", text: `The permanent operational rhythm of an elite company. It involves dedicating a specific monthly boardroom meeting and a recurring financial budget exclusively to testing future assumptions, rather than just reviewing past production metrics.` },
      { type: "h2", text: `Thin-Slicing` },
      { type: "p", text: `The act of taking a massive, multi-million-rupee strategic idea and cutting away 99% of the operational complexity, leaving only a tiny, cheap, highly inefficient 1% sliver that directly tests the Deal Killer assumption.` },
